s            Female mice exposed to PFOS had statistically significant decreased AVPV-Kiss1 mRNA and immunoreactive kisspeptin neurons leading to statistically significant decreased GnRH hormone.            Wang et al. (2018)                  Mice (Mus musculus)            60 days            50 ug/kg/bw BPA            yes            yes            Female mice exposed to BPA had statistically significant decreased AVPV-Kiss1 mRNA and immunoreactive kisspeptin neurons leading to statistically significant decreased GnRH hormone.&nbsp; Separate trial with kisspeptin was able to restore GnRH hormone levels.            Tang et al. (2020)                  Mice (Mus musculus)            42 days            5 mg/kg/d PFHxS            yes            yes            Female mice exposed to PFHxS had statistically significant decreased AVPV-Kiss1 mRNA and immunoreactive kisspeptin neurons leading to statistically decreased GnRH mRNA.&nbsp; Separate trial with kisspeptin was able to restore GnRH hormone levels.            Yin et al. (2021)", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 16:19:49 +0000 2026"}